{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place Parmesan into mixing bowl and grate <nobr>10 sec\/speed 9<\/nobr>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside.","Place chives, flour, polenta, eggs, milk, oil and 40 g of the reserved Parmesan into mixing bowl and blend <nobr>30 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Transfer into a jug and set aside. Clean and dry mixing bowl.","Preheat oven to 220°C. Set aside a shallow ovenproof baking dish (25 cm).","Place spring onions\/shallots into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add butter and spinach and sauté <nobr>5 min\/100°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>, stirring with aid of spatula, until spinach  wilts.","Add ricotta, salt and pepper and mix <nobr>5 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>.","Place a frying pan (20 cm) over medium-high heat and add 1 teaspoon of butter. Stir reserved batter and pour approx. ⅓ cup into frying pan, swirling pan as you add batter to cover base completely. Cook for 2 minutes, on 1 side only, until edges are golden, then transfer onto a plate, cooked side down. Stir batter and repeat frying, adding a teaspoon of butter after each crespelle (makes 8 crespelle - see Tips).","Transfer 1 crespelle into the base of reserved baking dish. Spread approximately 3 tablespoons of the spinach mixture onto 1 crespelle, smoothing with spatula. Place another crespelle on top, then spread with a further 3 tablespoons of spinach mixture. Continue layering crespelle and spinach mixture, finishing with a crespelle (make 8 crespelle in total).","Pour cream over crespelle \"cake\" and sprinkle with remaining 40 g grated Parmesan. Bake for 5 minutes (220°C). Reset oven setting to grill and grill for 1-2 minutes, until golden brown and bubbling. Scatter with chopped chives before serving (see Tips)."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["80 g Parmesan cheese, cut into pieces (3 cm)","5 sprigs fresh chives, cut into quarters, plus extra chopped for garnishing","120 g plain flour","2 tbsp po